by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-7-119, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection (b) and redesignating the existing subsections (b) and (c)
accordingly:
(b)
(1) Subject to subdivision (b)(2), a child under twenty-four (24) years of
age shall receive a twenty-five percent (25%) discount on tuition to the state
institution of higher education in which the child is enrolled if the child's parent is
a full-time employee of a public school system in this state in a position other
than the positions described in subdivisions (a)(1)(A) and (a)(1)(B), including, but
not limited to, full-time administrative staff, custodial staff, transportation
personnel, food service workers, and other full-time employees.
(2) The tuition discount established in subdivision (b)(1) is only available
in an academic year for which the general assembly has appropriated to the
state institution of higher education a sum sufficient to offset the loss of revenue
resulting from the tuition discount established in subdivision (b)(1).
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it, and
applies to the 2025-2026 academic year and each academic year thereafter.
